        "content": "Denial of service via unbounded loop over user-controlled array\n\ndistributeRewards iterates over an array that any user can grow by registering. Once the array is large enough the loop exceeds the block gas limit and the function permanently reverts, locking funds. Fix: use a pull-payment pattern and bound iteration; never loop over unbounded, externally-growable arrays.",
